        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(extensions): add adaptive-tone emotional intelligence plugin",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nWhat problem does this PR solve?\nThis PR introduces the **Adaptive Tone** built-in extension in OpenClaw under `extensions/adaptive-tone`. This plugin adjusts the assistant's conversational register dynamically based on time of day, channel register, repeated questions, unwell/distressed wellbeing phrases, and local weather conditions.\n\nWhy does this matter now?\nIt adds an emotional intelligence extension layer to the OpenClaw assistant, allowing more personalized and context-aware responses without requiring core system changes.\n\nWhat is the intended outcome?\nA modular, fully-tested extension loaded seamlessly by OpenClaw's plugin architecture.\n\nWhat is intentionally out of scope?\n- Persistent database storage of weather history (handled via 15-minute in-memory cache).\n- Direct modification of OpenClaw's prompt generation core (safely intercepts via `before_prompt_build` hook interface).\n\nWhat does success look like?\n1. The extension starts up cleanly when registered.\n2. Hook instructions merge weather and state parameters accurately.\n3. Cache works, and fetch fails open when APIs are unreachable.\n4. Unit/integration tests pass cleanly.\n\nWhat should reviewers focus on?\n- Hook injection logic in `index.ts`.\n- Weather API fetch caching and fallback mechanisms in `src/weather.ts`.\n\n## Linked context\n\nWhich issue does this close?\nCloses #\n\nWhich issues, PRs, or discussions are related?\nRelated #\n\nWas this requested by a maintainer or owner?\nNo, contributor-submitted extension.\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Integration of Adaptive Tone extension with weather-based tone adjustments.\n- Real environment tested: Local Windows environment running node v22.11.0.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\n  1. Ran `npm run build` to compile the TypeScript sources.\n  2. Ran `npm run test` to execute the full unit and integration test suite.\n- Evidence after fix (screenshot, recording, terminal capture, console output, redacted runtime log, linked artifact, or copied live output):\n  ```\n  > openclaw-adaptive-tone@0.1.0 test\n  > vitest run\n\n   RUN  v2.1.9 C:/Users/akash/Downloads/openclaw-adaptive-tone/openclaw-adaptive-tone\n\n   ✓ test/weather.test.ts (25 tests) 12ms\n   ✓ test/states.test.ts (12 tests) 10ms\n   ✓ test/signals.test.ts (13 tests) 39ms\n\n   Test Files  3 passed (3)\n        Tests  50 passed (50)\n     Start at  21:28:37\n     Duration  760ms (transform 292ms, setup 0ms, collect 404ms, tests 61ms, environment 1ms, prepare 591ms)\n  ```\n- Observed result after fix: 50 tests passed successfully covering weather cache, hook integration, time-of-day register adjustments, channel register adjustments, and distressed wellbeing phrases.\n- What was not tested: Long-term cache persistence across system reboots.\n- Proof limitations or environment constraints: None.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\nWhich commands did you run?\n- `npm run typecheck`\n- `npm run build`\n- `npm run test`\n\nWhat regression coverage was added or updated?\n- 25 tests for Weather API cache, fetch and fail-open behaviors.\n- 12 tests for Wellbeing and Time-of-day state behaviors.\n- 13 tests for Channel and Repetition signals.\n\nWhat failed before this fix, if known?\nN/A (New extension).\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\nYes (Tone changes based on context).\n\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\nYes (Adds a new adaptive-tone plugin config).\n\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\nYes (Performs HTTP requests to Open-Meteo weather API).\n\nWhat is the highest-risk area?\nExternal API dependency (Open-Meteo API).\n\nHow is that risk mitigated?\nImplemented a robust 15-minute in-memory cache and a fail-open fetch mechanism so that if the Weather API is slow or unreachable, it falls back to a neutral tone prompt without blocking the main conversational flow.\n\n## Current review state\n\nWhat is the next action?\nWaiting for maintainer review and clawsweeper CI verification.\n\nWhat is still waiting on author, maintainer, CI, or external proof?\nCI checks are currently running.\n",
